description: Perhaps the most magnificent thing that nature ever selected, this is "goblet moss,"urn moss," or "most magnificent thing ever moss." Physcomitrium pyriforme is a (typically) annual moss of arable sites. Sperm and egg swiped right in late fall/early winter and these sporophytes, nearly mature, will be ripe in just a few weeks. OMLA (Ohio Moss and Lichen Association) is assisting Rafael Medina, a researcher at Augustana College in Illinois who is studying polyploidy in this species, by collecting ripe specimens to send to his team. Details are on the OMLA web site https://ohiomosslichen.org/
